  "body": "**I'm submitting a...**\r\n  - [ ] Feature request\r\n  - [x] Bug report\r\n\r\n### Bug Report\r\n\r\nWhen you try to send a transaction (either a token transfer or coin transfer), you always recive a notification anouncing you're transffering from a contract. Apart from that, the ammount isn't displayed \r\nneither.\r\n\r\nI guess the main cause is the way `tokenTransferTo` variable it's handled. This state variable is initialized as an empty string `''` and then `TransactionNotification` component validates it trying to disinguish from null and undefined, when: \r\n\r\n```\r\n> '' !== undefined\r\n> true\r\n\r\n> '' !== null\r\n> true\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Where can this be found?\r\n\r\nIn order to display transaction notification correctly, `TransactionNotification` component validates transactions this way\r\n\r\n```\r\n//TransactionNotificaction.vue\r\n\r\n<li v-if=\"isTokenTransfer\">\r\n  <p>Via contract:</p>\r\n  ...\r\n</li>\r\n\r\nisTokenTransfer() {\r\n  return (\r\n   this.notice.body.tokenTransferTo !== undefined &&\r\n   this.notice.body.tokenTransferTo !== null\r\n  );\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nOn the other hand, `tokenTransferTo` state variable is initialized in `ConfirmModal` component:\r\n\r\n```\r\n//ConfirmModal.vue\r\n\r\ndata() {\r\n  return {\r\n    ...\r\n    tokenTransferTo: '',\r\n    ...\r\n  };\r\n},\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Repreducing the bug\r\n\r\nTo reproduce this you only need to send a transaction and check notifications status, then you'll see a new notification displaying:\r\n- Undefined ammount\r\n- \"Via contract\" (even if it isn't via contract)\r\n\r\nLike this\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11727247/59943463-b529b680-9438-11e9-821e-ef1f307ab718.png)\r\n\r\n### Posible solutions\r\n- Initialize `tokenTransferTo` as `null` or `undefined`\r\n- Change `isTokenTransfer()` to validate `''` input instead of `null` or `undefined`\r\n\r\n### Environment\r\n- Operating system: Ubuntu 18.04\r\n- Browser and version: Google Chrome, Version 74.0.3729.131 (Official Build) (64-bit)\r\n",
